12/07/2006
PODGORICA, Montenegro -- President Filip Vujanovic announced on Tuesday (11 July) that he has scheduled parliamentary and local elections to be held on 10 September. By law, political parties must submit their lists of candidates to election commissions by 16 August. The next Montenegrin parliament will have 81 deputies, instead of the current 75, and is tasked with adopting a new constitution for the country. 
In other news, Montenegro celebrates Statehood Day on Thursday. The presidents of Serbia, Croatia and Slovenia are expected to attend, along with representatives of the EU. (Vijesti, Pobjeda, Novi list - 12/07/06; Mina - 11/07/06)
